## Top 10 actionable remaining items in `chyren-web`

### 1) **`/api/chat/stream` uses `GROQ_API_KEY` with an empty-string fallback**
If `GROQ_API_KEY` is missing, `createGroq({ apiKey: '' })` will still be constructed and the first request will likely fail at runtime (harder to diagnose than an explicit 500 w/ clear error).

```18:21:/home/mega/Chyren/omega_workspace/workspace/OmegA-Next/chyren-web/app/api/chat/stream/route.ts
function getModel() {
  const groq = createGroq({ apiKey: process.env.GROQ_API_KEY ?? '' })
  return groq(process.env.GROQ_MODEL ?? 'llama-3.3-70b-versatile')
}
```

### 2) **Cron endpoint `/api/cron/warm-context` has no auth gate**
Vercel Cron will hit it, but so can anyone else; it calls `getRYContext()` and returns metadata. If you intended to protect it with `CRON_SECRET`, the route needs to validate `Authorization` (deploy script already sends it).

```17:27:/home/mega/Chyren/omega_workspace/workspace/OmegA-Next/chyren-web/app/api/cron/warm-context/route.ts
async function runWarm() {
  const start = Date.now()
  try {
    const context = await getRYContext()
    const ms = Date.now() - start
    return Response.json({ ok: true, length: context.length, ms })
  } catch (err) {
    const ms = Date.now() - start
    console.error('[warm-context] error:', (err as Error)?.message)
    return Response.json({ ok: false, error: (err as Error)?.message, ms }, { status: 500 })
  }
}
```

### 3) **Deploy script warms a hard-coded production URL**
`deploy-vercel.sh` always POSTs to `chyren-web.vercel.app` (even for previews/custom domains), so warmup can target the wrong deployment.

```22:28:/home/mega/Chyren/omega_workspace/workspace/OmegA-Next/chyren-web/scripts/deploy-vercel.sh
if [[ "$*" == *"--prod"* ]]; then
  echo "Warming Neon context cache..."
  curl -sf -X POST "https://chyren-web.vercel.app/api/cron/warm-context" \
    -H "Authorization: Bearer ${CRON_SECRET:-}" \
    -w "  HTTP:%{http_code} TIME:%{time_total}s\n" || echo "  (warmup skipped — CRON_SECRET not set or endpoint error)"
fi
```

### 4) **Env sync script only pushes `NEXT_PUBLIC_API_BASE_URL`**
If you want Firebase AI Logic active, the script doesn’t push any `NEXT_PUBLIC_FIREBASE_*` vars (despite `lib/firebase.ts` instructing you to do so).

```34:36:/home/mega/Chyren/omega_workspace/workspace/OmegA-Next/chyren-web/scripts/sync-vercel-env-from-one-true.sh
sync_one NEXT_PUBLIC_API_BASE_URL

echo "Done. vercel env list"
```

### 5) **Build-time context generation depends on `OMEGA_DB_URL` but nothing provisions it**
`scripts/generate-context.mjs` (run on `prebuild`) silently writes empty context if `OMEGA_DB_URL` isn’t set—so prod can “work” but without RAG.

```38:44:/home/mega/Chyren/omega_workspace/workspace/OmegA-Next/chyren-web/scripts/generate-context.mjs
async function fetchContext() {
  const url = process.env.OMEGA_DB_URL
  if (!url) { console.warn('[gen-context] OMEGA_DB_URL not set — skipping'); return '' }

  const conn = parseConnectionString(url)
  if (!conn) { console.warn('[gen-context] invalid connection string'); return '' }
```

### 6) **Generated context is currently empty (RAG effectively off)**
Right now `getRYContext()` returns `""`, meaning your system prompt enrichment is not happening.

```1:5:/home/mega/Chyren/omega_workspace/workspace/OmegA-Next/chyren-web/lib/generated-context.ts
// AUTO-GENERATED at build time by scripts/generate-context.mjs
// Do not edit manually — regenerated on every `npm run build`.

export const GENERATED_RY_CONTEXT: string = ""
```

### 7) **`NEXT_PUBLIC_API_BASE_URL` is baked at build time with a `localhost:8080` fallback**
If builds happen outside your expected environment, clients can ship with a bad API base URL. This also conflicts with the Dockerfile comment implying runtime configuration.

```4:14:/home/mega/Chyren/omega_workspace/workspace/OmegA-Next/chyren-web/next.config.ts
function publicApiBaseUrl(): string {
  if (process.env.NEXT_PUBLIC_API_BASE_URL) {
    return process.env.NEXT_PUBLIC_API_BASE_URL
  }
  if (process.env.VERCEL_URL) {
    return `https://${process.env.VERCEL_URL}`
  }
  return 'http://localhost:8080'
}
```

### 8) **Brain-state SSE stream ends after ~30s (60 ticks * 500ms)**
If the UI expects continuous telemetry, it will stop updating unless the client reconnect logic exists (not obvious from the route alone).

```13:31:/home/mega/Chyren/omega_workspace/workspace/OmegA-Next/chyren-web/app/api/brain-state/route.ts
const maxTicks = 60
let tick = 0

while (tick < maxTicks) {
  // ...
  tick++
  await new Promise((r) => setTimeout(r, 500))
}
```

### 9) **Rate-limit cache strategy may not behave consistently outside Vercel Runtime Cache**
Local dev falls back to in-memory `Map` (per-process). On serverless/scale-out, rate limiting becomes per-instance unless Runtime Cache is enabled and working.

```7:33:/home/mega/Chyren/omega_workspace/workspace/OmegA-Next/chyren-web/lib/hardening.ts
// Falls back to in-memory when Runtime Cache is unavailable (local dev)
const localStore = new Map<string, number[]>()

export async function checkRateLimit(ip: string): Promise<boolean> {
  // ...
  try {
    const cache = getCache({ namespace: 'hardening' })
    // ...
  } catch {
    // Runtime Cache unavailable (local dev) — fall back to in-memory
    // ...
  }
}
```

### 10) **`vercel.json` uses `npm install` instead of `npm ci`**
This can introduce lockfile drift / nondeterminism in installs compared to local + Docker (`npm ci`). If you want strict reproducibility, align these.

```3:6:/home/mega/Chyren/omega_workspace/workspace/OmegA-Next/chyren-web/vercel.json
"framework": "nextjs",
"installCommand": "npm install",
"buildCommand": "npm run build",
"crons": [
```

